%h2 User Record

- fp = @user.facebook_profile


.pseudo-table-striped
  .row-fluid.pseudo-table-row
    .span2 Name
    .span2= fp.name
    .span2= image_tag fp.image
  .row-fluid.pseudo-table-row
    .span2 UID
    .span2= fp.uid
  .row-fluid.pseudo-table-row
    .span2 Joined on
    .span2= fp.joined_on || '&mdash;'.html_safe


%h2 Facebook Profile Record

%div
  .row-fluid.pseudo-table-header
    %b.span2 Field
    %b.span4 Value
.pseudo-table-striped
  .row-fluid.pseudo-table-row
    .span2 Profile Maturity
    .span2= fp.profile_maturity || '&mdash;'.html_safe
    .span4
      .red-green-bar
        %span
          0
        %span.pull-right
          100
      %div
        %span{style: "position: relative; left: #{fp.profile_maturity}%"}
          ^
    .span4
      %p
        The Maturity Score tells us how much effort the user has invested into
        their profile over time. Variables that enter here include the number of friends,
        age of the profile. Higher scores here imply a greater relevance and
        confidence of the other scores.

  .row-fluid.pseudo-table-row
    .span2 Trust Score
    .span2= fp.trust_score || '&mdash;'.html_safe
    .span4
      .red-green-bar
        %span
          0
        %span.pull-right
          100
      %div
        %span{style: "position: relative; left: #{fp.trust_score}%"}
          ^
    .span4
      %p
        The Trust Score is a measure of the real-world social engagement of the user
        with their community.


%h2 User info

.pseudo-table-striped
  .row-fluid.pseudo-table-row
    .span2 User Stat
    .span2= display_stats(fp)
  -#.row-fluid.pseudo-table-row
  -#  .span2 User info
  -#  .span2= fp.info || '&mdash;'.html_safe
  .row-fluid.pseudo-table-row
    .span2 Location
    .span2
      = gmaps(markers: { data: friend_location},
        circles: {data: default_circle, option:{fillColor:"#FF0000"}},
        map_options: { bounds: [{lat: 37, lng: -121}, {lat: 38, lng: -123}].to_json, auto_adjust: true })
